'''{{Path|/etc/portage/package.use}}''' provides a more fine grained [[Handbook:Parts/Working/USE#Declaring_USE_flags_for_individual_packages|per-package control]] of [[USE flag|USE flags]] than the <code>USE=</code> line of {{Path|[[:/etc/portage/make.conf#USE|/etc/portage/make.conf]]}}.

{{Note|{{Path|/etc/portage/package.use}} can either be a single file or a directory containing per-package [[Handbook:Parts/Working/USE#Declaring_USE_flags_for_individual_packages|files]].}}

The {{Path|/etc/portage/package.use}} file or directory will override settings coming from the <code>USE=</code> line of {{Path|[[:/etc/portage/make.conf#USE|/etc/portage/make.conf]]}}.

== Example ==

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/portage/package.use|title=Example with this location as a single file|lang=ini|1=
# Globally disable the unwanted USE Flags which were enabled by the profile
*/* -bluetooth -consolekit -dbus -ldap -libnotify -nls -qt3support -udisks

# enable the offensive USE flag for app-admin/sudo
app-admin/sudo offensive

# disable mysql support for dev-lang/php
dev-lang/php -mysql 

# enable java and set the python interpreter version for libreoffice-5.1
app-office/libreoffice java PYTHON_SINGLE_TARGET: python3_4
}}

For more details see [[Handbook:Parts/Working/USE#Declaring_USE_flags_for_individual_packages|the Handbook]].

== Format ==

* One <var>DEPEND</var> atom per line with space-delimited [[Handbook:Parts/Working/USE|USE flags]] (see [[version specifier]] for information on <var>DEPEND</var> atom syntax).
* Comment lines begin with <code>#</code> (hash).

== Automatically generated content ==

{{c|emerge}} has the <code>--autounmask</code> option enabled by default (see {{c|man 1 emerge}}), so it can generate {{Path|package.use}} settings as necessary to satisfy dependencies.

